Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
rcOut(25.10)                                                      rcOut(25.10)

Name
       rcOut  - Reads the parasitic database and outputs the parasitics in the
       Standard Parasitic Exchange Format (SPEF)

Syntax
        rcOut

       [-help]

       [-excludeIlm]

       [-noRes]

       [-useEEQCellWithLibertyInfo]

       {{{-spef <fileName>}[-excNetFile <fileName> | -net <fileName>  |  -net-
       Name <list_of_nets>]}}

       [-view <viewName> | -rc_corner <rcCornerName>]

       [-cUnit {pF fF}]

       Reads the parasitic database and outputs the parasitics in the Standard
       Parasitic Exchange Format (SPEF).

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each rcOut parameter. For a  detailed  description
              of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man command:

               man rcOut

       -cUnit <unit>
              Specifies the unit of capacitance as fF or pF in the output SPEF
              file.

              Default: pF

       -excludeIlm
              Writes out only the top-level SPEF while excluding the ILM para-
              sitics.

              Note:  When  this  parameter  is specified, the top cell-name is
              suffixed in the SPEF output filename.

              For example, if test.spef is the  name  of  the  SPEF  file  and
              top_cell_name is the cell-name, then when you run below command:

              rcOut -spef test.spef -excludeIlm

              The output SPEF filename will be:

              test.spef.top_cell_name

       -excNetFile <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the file that contains nets to be excluded
              from the output file.

       -net <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the input file that contains the net names
              to be extracted.

              Default: Extracts all net names

       -netName <list_of_nets>
              Specifies the names of the nets to be written in the SPEF file.

              Default: Writes all nets

       -noRes Generates  a  SPEF  file without the resistance information. The
              SPEF file generated by this parameter can only be  used  to  im-
              prove  the  performance  of third-party simulator tools in early
              stages of the design.

              Caution: Most tools expect  the  resistance  information  to  be
              present  in  the SPEF file for performing extraction. Therefore,
              SPEF files with no resistance information  should  not  be  used
              with Ostrich for RC correlation.

       -rc_corner <rcCornerName>
              Specifies  the  RC corner that is used to generate the parasitic
              output file in the multi-corner flow.

       -spef <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the SPEF output file.

              If you add .gz as a suffix, the rcOut command automatically com-
              presses the generated file.

       -useEEQCellWithLibertyInfo
              Writes EEQ master cell in case the EEQ cells are present.

       -view <viewName>
              Specifies that the RC corner associated with the specified  view
              is  used  to  generate  the output SPEF file in the multi-corner
              flow.

Examples
              * Use any of the commands listed below  to  read  the  parasitic
                database  created during RC extraction and write parasitic in-
                formation for two nets for corner1 in SPEF format to the spec-
                ified file:

                rcOut -spef spefFile -rc_corner corner1 -netName [  list  net1
                net2 ]

                OR  rcOut  -spef  spefFile  -rc_corner  corner1 -netName {net1
                net2}

                OR

                rcOut -spef spefFile -rc_corner corner1 -netName "net1 net2"

